#5775 Lead QA contract OLG  North York 1 year contract.  Best rates apply. Communication is the key
please send resume to judy.chencareer@gmail.com or call 6478652985
Its a QA Lead/BA, going into an organization to set up the test environment from scratch.  
Major part of this role will be communication with the business to figure out exactly how 
to set up proper test cases.  
Position Summary: Under the direction of the IT Operations Manager, 
TSG, the Senior Quality Assurance Analyst is responsible 
for developing and establishing quality assurance standards and measures 
for the information technology services within the organization.
This individual will also gather and analyze data in support of business cases, 
proposed projects, and systems requirements. This will include writing test plans and 
scripts for tracking defects and fixes in product development, software application development,
information systems, and operations systems, creating test documentation and 
performing functional, regression, and end-to-end testing on multiple systems.

#5821 Quality Engineer RBC DT
Please send resume to judy.chencareer@gmail.com or call 6478652985
Must Have:
3+ years of professional Quality Engineering and or development experience with proficiency in quality processes, test deliverables, defining Test Strategies, Test Plans and evaluating Risk Coverage.
Hands-on experience on automated testing for User interface, database and reporting, using tools ETL, Selenium, Python scripting, Appium, ROBOT Framework or other Keyword Driven test automation frameworks.
Knowledge and experience on distributed applications using Java, Advanced SQL, Unix (Linux) technologies.
Knowledge on DevOps with integrated build and testing using SVN, Jenkins, Nexus / UrbanCode, Robot Framework.
Experience working in an Agile environment using Jira, HPQC ALM
Expert in requirement testability review and hands-on experience on performance testing.

Please send resume to judy.chencareer@gmail.com or call 6478652985
5-7 years of experience in design / user experience with a strong desire to focus on user-centered design and responsive designs 
Solid UX Practice/Process 
University degree or certification in User Experience related field or equivalent work experience 
Solid portfolio demonstrating impactful customer experiences, including experience developing digital products from initial concept through to implementation.
